s a initialize click counter to zero upon creation, I want to set click counter to zero when a short link is created, so
 that stats endpoint returns click_count=0 for the new link.Priority: medium**Acceptance criteria for this story (compon
ent-level — your task may satisfy only the subset within its scope):**- **AC-US-001-4-D-001** — After POST, GET /{slug}/
stats returns JSON with click_count=0  Measurable: GET /{slug}/stats returns {"click_count":0} immediately after link cr
eation## Non-Functional Requirements That Apply- **NFR-006** (compliance): EU sharers must provide GDPR consent before s
hortening.  Threshold: Zero URL shortening requests originating from EU IP addresses are processed without an explicit G
DPR consent flag.  Measurement: Middleware intercepts all shorten requests, verifies GDPR_consent=true for EU-origin IPs
; audit logs record consent status and origin; nightly compliance report aggregates violations for human review.- **NFR-
008** (security): Reject URLs exceeding 2048 characters and non-http(s) schemes with HTTP 400.  Threshold: Zero requests
 with URL length >2048 characters or non-http(s) schemes are rejected; all such requests must return HTTP 400.  Measurem
ent: Automated integration test harness runs on every deploy, submitting URLs of up to 3000 characters and various non-h
ttp(s) schemes (ftp, file, data, etc.) and asserting the response status code is 400; runtime request logs are monitored
 for any non-400 responses to over-long or unsupported scheme URLs.## Component ContractComponent: `comp-click-counter-i
nitializer` — Click Counter Initializer ServiceDomain: `domain-slug-creation`Responsibilities:- `resp-cc-001`: Initializ
e click counter to zero upon creation of a short link.## Data Models You May Read/Write### DM-click-counter-initializer-
mapping — MappingFields:- `slug`: `string` _(primary_key)_- `original_url_encrypted`: `string` _(not_null)_- `click_coun
t`: `integer` _(default=0, check>=0)_- `consent_flag`: `boolean` _(default=false)_- `created_at`: `timestamp` _(default=
current_timestamp)_- `updated_at`: `timestamp` _(on_update=current_timestamp)_## Component Test Cases (context — may bel
ong to sibling tasks; your gate is the Completion Criteria, not these)### TC-delta-1 (functional) — verifies AC-US-001-4
-D-001Preconditions:- System is deployed and reachableExpected outcome: AC-US-001-4-D-001 holds true## How This Componen
t Is Evaluated (context — these are component/system-level methods, not your task's unit of work)- Target `US-001` (func
tional)  Method: Automated API test suite using Postman/Newman covering URL validation, slug format verification ([A-Za-
z0-9]{6}), consent flag metadata retrieval via /{slug}/metadata, statistics retrieval immediately after creation (/stats
/{slug}) and duplicate slug uniqueness with two simultaneous POST requests. Each request is timed to ensure GET /{slug} 
redirects within 1 second.  Success: All sub-tests pass: status codes match acceptance criteria, slug matches regex, met
adata consent flag reflects input, stats click_count equals 0 after creation, duplicate slugs are distinct and both redi
rect correctly.- Target `NFR-006` (quality)  Method: Inspect network traffic and application logs for X-EU-IP=true entri
es; verify that any 201 responses include consent:true.  Success: Zero URL shortening requests from EU IPs processed wit
hout explicit GDPR consent flag- Target `NFR-008` (quality)  Method: Run ZAP spider to generate payloads exceeding limit
s and different schemes, verify responses.  Success: Zero requests with URL length >2048 characters or non-http(s) schem
es are accepted; all such return HTTP 400.## Technical Constraints (apply without exception)- **TECH-PGSQL-16** [Postgre
SQL] (database): Persistence: Postgres 16+ on a single managed instance.- **TECH-HTTPS-ONLY** [HTTPS] (security): Transp
ort: HTTPS only on all public endpoints; HTTP requests redirect to HTTPS.- **TECH-CONTAINERIZED-SERVICE** (deployment): 
Runtime: a single containerised service; no microservices.- **TECH-JSON-LOGS-STDOUT** (monitoring): Observability: struc
tured JSON logs to stdout; logs ingested by the platform's standard log aggregator.- **TECH-AES256-ENCRYPTION** [AES-256
] (security): The original URLs stored in the mappings table must be encrypted at rest using AES-256 because the URLs ma
y incidentally contain personally identifying or session tokens.  Rationale: Because URLs may incidentally contain perso
nally identifying or session tokens.## Compliance / V&V / Quality Items That Apply- **COMP-GDPR-APPLIES-EU** (compliance
): The service is offered globally; GDPR applies to EU sharers.- **QA-1** (quality_attribute): URL validation must rejec
t URLs exceeding 2048 characters and non-http(s) schemes with a 400 status codeREQUIRED OUTPUT:[JC:SYSTEM SCOPE]You are 
